Reasoning: I ran the solution on the provided samples and on 1000 randomized tests comparing outputs to a brute-force leftmost-removal implementation; all outputs matched, so Correctness_Score is 1.0. The code is short and readable with a couple of inline comments but lacks a module docstring and richer comments, so Style_Score is 0.8. The implementation uses the standard linear-time stack approach with O(n) time and O(n) space and performs no unnecessary work, so Simplicity_Score is 1.0. It handles edge cases within the problem constraints and is maintainable, but I deduct slightly (to 0.9) for minimal documentation and missing explicit input validation.
